# UI Toolkit

- USS is Unity's CSS subset. Verify properties and selectors against Unity 2021.3 docs,
  not current browser CSS documentation.
- Use supported flex layout. Do not assume CSS Grid, `calc`, `min`, `max`, `clamp`,
  media queries, generated content, or structural pseudo-selectors work.
- Keep UXML structural, USS visual, and C# behavioral. Use inline style only for values
  that genuinely depend on runtime geometry or state.
- Prefer stable, shallow class selectors. Avoid selectors coupled to deep hierarchy.
- Cache repeated `Q()` results and register/unregister callbacks symmetrically.
- Preserve existing naming and style-sheet organization in each package; do not impose
  game-specific BEM or theme architecture on legacy UI.
- Test editor UI in its actual panel/inspector context when behavior depends on attachment,
  geometry, focus, or scheduling.
